40|$|Work in two volumes. Volume 1. National studies. [...] volume 2. Comparative analyses. A team of European social {{scientists}} investigated the various facets of increased militancy {{in the late}} 1960 s. The results are contained in individual essays, which {{take account of the}} changes that preceded and were accentuated by the economic crisis of 1973. The first volume deals with the increase in <b>industrial</b> <b>conflicts</b> and the consequences in the major European countries; the second volume takes up the more general problems - inter alia, the role of women and immigrants, the changing role of the state and of the politics of the trade unions. A major effort at clarification and analysis...|$|R
