50|$|The {{threats of}} wild cat {{industrial}} action {{on a national}} level convinced the Federal Parliament to adopt a system of compulsory registration of unions, and compulsory arbitration in disputes. The Conciliation and Arbitration Act was assented to in 1904, and dictated the terrain of <b>industrial</b> relations <b>conflicts</b> and unionism until the 1990s.|$|R
